## Deployment

This project ships with semver-tag-driven deploy scripts (`deploy.sh`, `deploy.ps1`) that build a Docker image and trigger a Portainer-style redeploy webhook.

```bash
./deploy.sh dev patch    # bump patch, build, push, redeploy dev stack
./deploy.sh prod minor   # bump minor, tag (on {{git.main_branch}}), push, redeploy prod stack

# Windows
.\deploy.ps1 prod patch
```

Required environment (in `.env` or environment):
- `PORTAINER_WEBHOOK_URL` — prod stack redeploy webhook
- `PORTAINER_DEV_WEBHOOK_URL` — dev stack redeploy webhook

Image: `{{deploy.image}}` (override by editing `IMAGE` in `deploy.sh` / `$Image` in `deploy.ps1`).

The `Dockerfile` is a starting point — adjust the build/runtime commands for your stack.

{{/if}}
